io.github.ddimitrov.nuggets

Class ReflectionProxy

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.ddimitrov.nuggets.ReflectionProxy

  • public class ReflectionProxy
extends Object

    Entry Point Provides a concise and expressive way for performing multiple reflective access operations, building on the Extractors class. As a reflection proxy has a final association with a single object, its API provides the (currently unused) opportunity for optimizations, such as memoizing methods annotated with Contract(@pure=true) and caching accessors and method/var handles.

      • invoke

        public ReflectionProxy invoke(@NotNull
                              @NotNull String name,
                              @Nullable
                              Object... args)

        Invokes a (potentially private) method on the wrapped object and returns the result wrapped in a new reflection proxy.

        Known deficiency - if a static method is shadowed by an instance method in the same type, the instance method will be preferred and there is no way to invoke the static one using this class.

        Parameters:
        name - the name of the method to invoke
        args - the actual arguments for the method
        Returns:
        the wrapped method return value
